<ProjectManifest name="B777_NMPC_FlightSimulator" version="1.0" language="en" created_for="Julian Kazmierski">
  <Metadata>
    <Title>Boeing 777-like Flight Dynamics Simulator with a Nonlinear MPC Autopilot in MATLAB/Simulink</Title>
    <ShortName>B777 NMPC Flight Simulator</ShortName>
    <MainGoal>Create a nonlinear flight-dynamics simulator for a Boeing 777-like large transport aircraft and an autopilot concept based on Nonlinear Model Predictive Control, including longitudinal, lateral-directional, LNAV/VNAV and ILS modes.</MainGoal>
    <ImportantNote>The project is not intended to reproduce a certified or exact Boeing 777 model. The goal is an engineering-oriented educational 777-like model based on public data, approximate aerodynamic models and validation against available performance references.</ImportantNote>
  </Metadata>
  <Assumptions>
    <Assumption>Baseline variant: the Boeing 777-300ER or the 777-200LR/300ER/F family is used as the ACAP-based reference class.</Assumption>
    <Assumption>Full simulation plant: a nonlinear 6-DOF model in Simulink, preferably using the Aerospace Blockset 6DOF Quaternion block.</Assumption>
    <Assumption>NMPC prediction model: a reduced model, initially separate for longitudinal and lateral-directional channels and later integrated.</Assumption>
    <Assumption>Detailed Boeing aerodynamic data are not public, so aerodynamic coefficients are approximated, calibrated and validated.</Assumption>
    <Assumption>The project is developed in MATLAB/Simulink using Aerospace Toolbox, Aerospace Blockset and Model Predictive Control Toolbox.</Assumption>
    <Assumption>A flyable and trimmable plant is developed first; NMPC implementation follows after that foundation exists.</Assumption>
  </Assumptions>
  <Toolchain>
    <Required>
      <Tool>MATLAB</Tool>
      <Tool>Simulink</Tool>
      <Tool>Aerospace Toolbox</Tool>
      <Tool>Aerospace Blockset</Tool>
      <Tool>Model Predictive Control Toolbox</Tool>
      <Tool>Optimization Toolbox</Tool>
      <Tool>Control System Toolbox</Tool>
      <Tool>Simulink Control Design</Tool>
    </Required>
    <Optional>
      <Tool>Stateflow for autopilot mode logic</Tool>
      <Tool>Simulink 3D Animation or FlightGear for visualisation</Tool>
      <Tool>OpenAP for performance validation</Tool>
      <Tool>DATCOM/OpenVSP/VSPAERO for aerodynamic-data estimation</Tool>
    </Optional>
  </Toolchain>
  <Architecture>
    <Description>The architecture consists of an FMS/MCP layer, a mode manager, a trajectory generator, NMPC controllers, flight-control allocation, actuator dynamics, a nonlinear 6-DOF plant and sensor models.</Description>
    <SignalFlow>
      <Step>B777-like FMS / MCP</Step>
      <Step>Mode Manager</Step>
      <Step>Trajectory Generator</Step>
      <Step>Nonlinear MPC</Step>
      <Step>Flight Control Allocation</Step>
      <Step>Actuator Dynamics</Step>
      <Step>B777-like 6-DOF Plant</Step>
      <Step>Sensors / ADC / IRS / Navigation</Step>
      <Step>Feedback to Autopilot</Step>
    </SignalFlow>
  </Architecture>
